<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-31T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/943: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-31T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                            1922—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>10. Your May 24th, noon.</p>
                            <p>You will inform the Government of Bolivia that the question of
                                Bolivia’s participation in the discussions which are now being
                                carried on between Chile and Peru, and which relate to questions
                                arising out of a treaty of which these two countries were the only
                                signatories, is a matter for the exclusive consideration of the two
                                countries <pb facs="0589" n="469" xml:id="pg_469"/> concerned, and
                                the Government of the United States regrets that it feels unable to
                                take any initiative in this matter.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>